climbs.name: Regular Route
climbs.fa: Andrew Emery and Steve Roper December 11, 1965

content.description: This route was originally rated 4th Class by the first ascentionists because there is no protection.  It's a fun scramble for those up to the challenge.  If you don't want to downclimb the route you can rappel from three bolts.
content.protection: No protection other than the three bolt anchor on top.
content.location: On the northeast side of the formation locate two digger pine trees. Head upwards by chimneying between the pines.

content.description:
The first fifteen feet of this route are very steep, but on good holds.  Don't blow it before clipping the first bolt or you might never escape from Soledad.  The crux is probably clipping the 2nd bolt with the pump factor and loose holds causing a bit of consternation.

To descend rappel from a three bolt anchor with lowering hardware.
content.protection: Three protection bolts to a three bolt anchor.
content.location: This route is located on the steep, northwest face.  You should be able to spot the first bolt.
